1. git init => to initialize a git ( creates a .git dir )
2. git config user.name "name"; git config user.email "email"
3. Working area   VS    Staging area    VS commited area 
4. git add <files names> => to add files to the staging area
5. git commit -m "message" => move files from staging area to commited area
6. git status => to see files in working,staging area
7. git log    => to see all commits 
8. .gitignore => add files that we don't want git to track here
9. git commit -am "message" => to add and commit only tracked files


1. git log --oneline => display the commits every commit in one line
2. git log --name-only => display the files changes in the commits
3. git log -n <number of commits> => display certain number of commits
4. HEAD => where are we now 
5. BRANCH => git creates a master branch by default and it's moved always to the latest commit 
